source.name: Medicaid income levels (ages 65 and up)
source.description: This table represents details of Medicaid income levels (ages 65 and up). Medicaid provides free health insurance for low-income older adults. Eligible adults receive their medical care through a managed care plan or fee-for-service. While ones application is being processed, Medicaid may provide up to 90 days of retroactive coverage for unpaid medical bills, if the individual is eligible during those 90 days.
